{
  "texts": [
    "The associated creation operator is ĉ † τ a (k).",
    "In the periodic gauge, the moiré cell-periodic functions |u τ a (k)⟩ = e -ik•r |ψ τ a (k)⟩ are not periodic in its momentum argument.",
    "In particular, we have |u τ,a (k + G)⟩ = e -iG•r |u τ,a (k)⟩, where G is a moiré RLV.",
    "We define the continuum model form factorλ τ,ab (k, q) = ⟨u τ,a (k)|u τ,b (k + q)⟩ = G,l,σ u * τ a;lσ (k, G)u τ b;lσ (k + q, G)(15)= λ * τ,ba (k + q, -q),(16)where k is a mBZ momentum, but q can be any (intravalley) momentum transfer.",
    "This is an important quantity since it encodes the Bloch structure of the wavefunctions and determines the flavour-diagonal density operatorsρτs (q) = k∈mBZ ab ĉ † τ as (k)λ τ,ab (k, q)ĉ τ bs (k + q),(17)where we have reintroduced the spin label s. Note that in the periodic gauge, λ τ,ab (k, q) is periodic (in the mBZ) in its first momentum argument, but not its second momentum argument.In terms of the form factors, the flavor-conserving part of the long-range density-density Coulomb Hamiltonian is Ĥint = 1 2A τ τ ′ ss ′ q∈all V (q): ρτs (q)ρ † τ ′ s ′ (q): ρ0 = 1 2A ss ′ τ τ ′ abcd q∈all k α,k β ∈mBZ V (q)λ τ,ab (k α, q)λ * τ ′,dc (k β, q) ×: ĉ † τ as (k α)ĉ † τ ′ cs ′ (k β + q)ĉ τ ′ ds ′ (k β)ĉ τ bs (k α + q): ρ 0, (18)where A is the total area of the system 14."
